description: Back-formation from prepensed, probably from Anglo-Norman prepenser.

entries.meaning: Devised, contrived, or planned beforehand; preconceived, premeditated.

verbs.description: prepense (third-person singular simple present prepenses, present participle prepensing, simple past and past participle prepensed)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To weigh or consider beforehand; to intend.
examples: All these thinges prepensed and gathered together seriously
